parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the starter motor can cause the vehicle to fail to start, leading to inconvenience, delays, and potential safety risks, especially if the vehicle is stranded in a hazardous location.
symptoms: The vehicle fails to start
grinding or buzzing noise when attempting to start
loud screeching or winding noise when turning the key
multiple attempts required to start the engine
warning indicators illuminated on the instrument panel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the starter can cause the vehicle to fail to start, leading to inconvenience and potentially leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Grinding or spinning noise on start-up
vehicle fails to start
multiple attempts required to start the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: Vehicle accelerates more than intended
failure to stop when braking
crash resulting in injuries and damage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine vibration and stalling can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents and injuries, as well as inconvenience and frustration.
symptoms: Engine vibration or shake while in drive mode
stalling at high speeds
hesitation when accelerating
low oil level
engine ticking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The misalignment of the starter motor can cause intermittent grinding, failure to engage, or spinning without starting the engine, leaving the driver stranded and potentially causing safety issues.
symptoms: The starter motor grinds intermittently
the starter motor spins without starting the engine
the starter motor does not engage when the start button is pressed
the vehicle fails to start.
